My dreams don't fade.
They never did and they never will.
I sleep dreaming about the things I can be.
I sleep dreaming about the things I can achieve.
I sleep knowing when I wake up, birds won't sing in my ears
Instead a alarm goes off in my ears, ringing in my ears, like a siren.
I sleep knowing I will never escape this infinte cycle.
But maybe in my dreams I will.
Maybe in my dreams I can rest,
Knowing that nothing there can wake me up.
But only if I could sleep.